content.description: Same start as Beetlewood (V1). Climb straight up the corner. Crux is the left hand sloper pull to the top out.

Sit start under the small roof adjacent to the rock on the ground (north side). Work your way right using good side pulls. Get to the good rail side-pull and top out. 

 [same start as Beetlewood Direct]

 *NO SUPER EASY WALK DOWN*
content.location: While walking along the Burr Oak trail, you'll eventually come to a spot where the trail has to squeeze between two large boulders. Beetlewood's boulder is behind the boulder on the left of the trail. There's a small gap (alley) behind the left boulder and the Beetlewood boulder with enough space to set up a couple pads.

content.description:
Fairly narrow crevice between two large boulders. Can (snugly) fit multiple pads and people for decent protection. There is one large rock below the routes that can be easily covered by a pad. Spotter recommended to keep the climber from hitting the rock on the other side of the trench/crevice.

 UNSURE OF WALK DOWN FOR THE TOP OUT
